questions.question:
The following program computes values of a mathematical function f(x). Determine the form of f(x).

main()
{
  int m, n;
  float x, y, t;
  scanf("%f%d", &x, &n);
  t = 1; y = 0; m = 1;
  do
  {
    t *= (-x / m);
    y += t;
  } while (m++ < n);
  printf("The value of y is %f", y);
}

A. e^x
B. e^(-x) - 1
C. 1 - e^(-x)
D. e^(-x)
